methods.funcNPoints:
Sets the number of data points in this dataset.

:param npoints: (int) - number of points
:return: (io.deephaven.db.plot.datasets.xy.XYDataSeriesFunction) this data series with the specified number of points.
methods.funcRange:
Sets the data range for this series.

*Overload 1*  
  :param xmin: (double) - range minimum
  :param xmax: (double) - range maximum
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.plot.datasets.xy.XYDataSeriesFunction) this data series with the new range
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param xmin: (double) - range minimum
  :param xmax: (double) - range maximum
  :param npoints: (int) - number of data points
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.plot.datasets.xy.XYDataSeriesFunction) this data series with the new range

text:
XYDataSeries based on a function.

 By default, this calculates at least 200 data points inside the plot's existing range. The number of points can be
 increased for a finer grained plot, or decreased if less resolution is needed. The points are recomputed as the
 Chart's x-range changes.
